HashSet Methods -->
Most Used -->
    set.add(value); -- Add element to the set
    set.contains(value); -- Check element exists
    set.remove(value); -- Remove element
    set.size(); -- Size of set
    set.isEmpty(); -- Check set empty or not
    set.clear(); -- Remove all elements
Commonly Used -->
    set.iterator(); -- Iterate elements
    set.toArray(); -- Convert set to array
    set.addAll(collection); -- Add all elements from another collection
    set.removeAll(collection); -- Remove elements of another collection
    set.containsAll(collection); -- Check all elements exist


HashMap Methods -->
Mostly Used -->
    map.put(key,value); -- Add key value pair
    map.get(key); -- Get value using key
    map.containsKey(key); -- Check key exists
    map.containsValue(value); -- Check value exists
    map.remove(key); -- Remove key value pair
    map.size(); -- Size of map
    map.isEmpty(); -- Check map empty
    map.clear(); -- Remove all entries
Commonly Used
    map.keySet(); -- Get all keys
    map.values(); -- Get all values
    map.entrySet(); -- Get key value pairs
    map.putAll(map2); -- Copy another map
    map.getOrDefault(key,defaultValue); -- Return default if key not found


